This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also employs the kernelization methodology of parameterized complexity analysis, which is a technique used in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also discusses experimental results on real-world graphs, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of linear-time data reduction rules, which is a technique used in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
